 :tx/rationale "MODEL-WIRE PROPOSAL: Wire Embedder into the CLI observe pipeline, replacing the hard-coded HashEmbedder. CURRENT STATE: observe.rs line 536 creates HashEmbedder unconditionally: 'let hash_embedder = HashEmbedder::new(DEFAULT_DIM); let obs_embedding = TextEmbedder::embed(&hash_embedder, args.text)'. PROPOSED STATE: The observe command receives a Box<dyn TextEmbedder> from the CLI entrypoint. The entrypoint tries to load model files; if successful, uses Embedder; otherwise HashEmbedder. The embedder is constructed ONCE at startup and shared across commands (not per-invocation). APPROACH: (1) Add an EmbedderFactory to the CLI crate that resolves the best available embedder. (2) Thread the embedder through ObserveArgs or a shared CLI context. (3) The observe command, status command, and harvest command all use the same embedder instance. (4) The innate concept datoms in init.rs should also use the model embedder when available — hash-embedded innate concepts vs model-embedded observations would have near-zero cosine. CRITICAL INVARIANT: innate concept embeddings and observation embeddings MUST use the same embedder. If init creates concepts with HashEmbedder but observe embeds with Embedder, cosine similarity is meaningless (different vector spaces). VERIFICATION: (A) When model present, cosine(innate_anomalies, 'ignored error returns') > JOIN_THRESHOLD. (B) When model absent, behavior is identical to current (hash embedder fallback). (C) Innate concepts are re-embedded on first observe if embedder type changed since init."
